# What These Packages Do
bashnpm install vite-plugin-pwa workbox-precaching @vitejs/plugin-react
1. vite-plugin-pwa
Purpose: Converts your React web app into a Progressive Web App (PWA)
What it does:

Creates a service worker automatically
Generates a web app manifest (app name, icon, theme colors)
Enables "Add to Home Screen" on mobile/desktop
Caches your app so it works offline
Handles push notifications

Without it: Your app is just a website. Can't install it. No offline support.
With it: Users can click "Install" and it appears like a native app on their phone/desktop.

2. workbox-precaching
Purpose: Smart caching strategy for your app files
What it does:

Automatically detects which files to cache (JS, CSS, HTML, images)
Puts them in browser's cache storage when app loads
Serves cached files even if server is down
Detects file changes and updates cache automatically

Without it: Service worker has to manually list what to cache (tedious, error-prone)
With it: Automatic intelligent caching. Set it and forget it.
Important Note for MindWell: We only cache the app shell (UI), NOT sensitive journal data (entries are encrypted server-side)

3. @vitejs/plugin-react
Purpose: Adds React support to Vite build tool
What it does:

Lets Vite understand JSX syntax (React's HTML-in-JS)
Fast Hot Module Replacement (HMR) - changes show instantly without refresh
Optimizes React for fast builds

Without it: Vite won't understand your .jsx files and won't compile them
With it: React code works seamlessly in Vite

Can I Skip These?
No - they're required for:
